node.text:
What would you rate this modern architectural home out of 1-10? 

In the Russian Capital of #Moscow, this contemporary home, set among the pine woods on an island in the Moskva River, introduces a revolutionary outward-looking approach to the city's architectural tradition.

Designed by SAOTA @_saota, a South African architecture studio known for advancing the possibilities of 20th-century modernism, this home represents the tradition of the terrace, with its emphasis on an outdoor orientation, but in a context and climatic condition vastly different from the origin of the type.

Interior design @maxkasymov @_arrcc 

Photography @sergeyananiev

node.text:
How beautiful is this waterfront property in #MiamiBeach ?

Lying on a property of over 24,000 total SF, 1600 W 25th St is a majestic 6 and 7 bath move-in ready home with a waterfront view of the Intercostal. Developer Brett Palos conveys the opulent lifestyle of French royalty through the grand façade and glamorous interior of this estate. Spanning over 12,000 SF of living space, the smart home holds a master bed wing, a rooftop terrace, and a chef’s kitchen. A seamless blend of indoor and outdoor living is created through its encasing of glass panels and a club room.  All of the windows in the club room open up to access the pool, outdoor seating, and gardens.

Sold for $21,795,000
By @esther_percal

Designed and built by @ramtin_ray_nosrati , comes one of the most anticipated & mesmerizing projects in Los Angeles for $44,000,000.

Towering gracefully above LA’s dazzling city lights, this newly built smart home of sweeping picturesque vistas throughout (including unobstructed Getty, city and ocean views), expansive & flat over 30,000 square foot exterior living space, striking water features, and a vast array of exquisite amenities delivers effortless resort-style living and elevated entertainment that will continually wow you and your guests alike.
